Seven bomb blasts rocked Jaipur, India, killing 80 and injuring 200 in a horrific terror attack.
Among the victims were a young boy, a bride, and a man on a bicycle rickshaw.
The international community, including Pakistan, the US, UK, and France, condemned the attacks.
Jaipur, a popular tourist destination, has been targeted before, with recent bombings in Hyderabad and Punjab.
Police arrested two suspects after the coordinated bombings, which aimed to incite religious tensions.
The US and Indian leaders denounced the violence, emphasizing the need to combat terrorism together.
